England defeated Wales 2-0 to
remain unbeaten in qualifying for soccerâ€™s 2012 European
Championship.  Frank Lampard  and  Darren Bent  scored goals in the first 15
minutes to give England the win at the Millennium Stadium in
Cardiff. England matches Montenegro with 10 points at the top of
qualifying Group G.  The winner in each of the nine groups, along with the
second-place team with the most points, qualify for Euro 2012
with hosts Poland and Ukraine. The remaining eight second-place
